other_tests.findings: Follicle-stimulating hormone, luteinizing hormone, and thyroid-stimulating hormone were all within the normal range; elevated prolactin level at 64.72 ng/ml (reference range 4.79–23.3).

Normal-sized uterus with two uterine cavities separated by a low T2 signal septum extending into the endocervical canal; surface of fundus convex with acute angle between uterine cavities (about 60°); regular endometrium about 7 mm in each cavity.
Confirmed presence of complete vaginal septum, cervical septum, and septum inside the uterus reaching the fundus, separating the uterus into two cavities.
Indicated a normal outer wall of the uterus.
Surgical intervention to remove the septum.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Followed by removal of septal remnants after 3 months.
